########################### Ubuntu Ceph Preconfig ##########################

This autoinstall file is meant for installing Ubuntu 22 and running the core commands present in our Ubuntu22 Ceph Preconfig script.

Highlights include the following:
-Configures two 32GB redundant boot drives using sda and sdb.
-Creates root user with password hash of "password".
-Creates user named "user" with password hash of "password1".
-Installs packages listed in script; enables Cockpit.
-Installs Cephadm (Squid by default) and Podman; pulls down set Ceph container for later use.
-Configures host to use root password SSH and networkmanager for networking.
-Installs firewalld, disables ufw, and sets a rule allowing Cockpit.
-Updates/upgrades host packages.

For further information on how to use this file, consult the guide here: http://192.168.1.91/doku45/doku.php?id=service:serv-ts-_testing_headless_rocky_install:network
